riplet-atf-carousel-04.jpg 612w","srcWebp":"/static/e1d4ee517416b4faf08f109ce3b2d480/7a328/pdp-triplet-atf-carousel-04.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/e1d4ee517416b4faf08f109ce3b2d480/b42dd/pdp-triplet-atf-carousel-04.webp 256w,\n/static/e1d4ee517416b4faf08f109ce3b2d480/e4e36/pdp-triplet-atf-carousel-04.webp 512w,\n/static/e1d4ee517416b4faf08f109ce3b2d480/7a328/pdp-triplet-atf-carousel-04.webp 612w","sizes":"(max-width: 612px) 100vw, 612px"}},"publicURL":"/static/e1d4ee517416b4faf08f109ce3b2d480/pdp-triplet-atf-carousel-04.jpg"},"imageAlt":null}]}],"attributes":[{"key":"Refillable","heading":"The Refill Revolution","subheading":"Reduce, Refill & Reuse, Recycle.","content":"<ul>\n  <li>Your glass Cleanser & Face Oil bottles are refillable. Fluff Refill pouches are recyclable with Soft Plastics through REDcycle once thoroughly cleaned.</li>\n  <li>We are working on Stage 2 of our refill model, which includes working on a solution that uses Sugarcane instead of plastic, however there exists no current option (that we have found) with a spout.</li>\n  <li>The refills are held in the compact with a very strong magnet.</li>\n  <li>Would putting our refills in a large glass or aluminum bottle defeat the purpose of a refill? Would it become too expensive? More than the product itself?</li>\n  <li>If you have any suggestions of how you'd like to receive refills, we'd love to know. </li>\n  <li>This is our first step to reducing the amount of single use primary bottles, in a long journey.</li>\n</ul>"},{"key":"100% Vegan","heading":"100% Vegan and Cruelty Free","subheading":"Products that are good for your skin, your thoughts, and the planet.","content":"<ul>\n  <li>Jojoba Oil has the closest botanical match to our skin's natural oil. It is full of antioxidants, omegas and vitamins A, D & E, providing moisture and nourishment for dry skin.</li>\n  <li>Hemp Seed Oil contains a high concentration of omega fatty acids with hydrating and anti-inflammatory benefits for the skin.</li>\n  <li>It is non-comedogenic meaning it won't clog pores, while regulating oil production which can help to prevent breakouts.</li>\n  <li>Ashwagandha Root has antibacterial and antimicrobial properties. </li>\n  <li>It also promotes the production of hyaluronan for hydration, and elastin for suppleness and collagen for skin strength. It can also help promote relaxation as a natural adaptogen.</li>\n  <li>Full Ingredient List - Cleanser: Withania somnifera (Ashwaganda) Herbal Water, Olea Europaea (Olive) Oil, Simmondsia Chinensis (Jojoba) Seed Oil, Aloe Barbadensis (Aloe Vera) Juice, Glycerin, Cannabis Sativa (Hemp) Seed Oil, Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter, Cetearyl Alcohol, Glyceryl Stearate Citrate, Xanthan Gum, Tocopheryl Acetate, Tocotrienols, Sodium Levulinate, Sodium Anisate. Face Oil #1: 100% Pure Certified Organic Jojoba Oil Face Oil #2: 100% Pure Meadowfoam Seed Oil 100% Unbleached, Muslin Cotton Face Wash Cloth.</li>\n</ul>"},{"key":"42 Day Returns","heading":"42 Day Return","subheading":"Our 42 Day Return Policy","content":"<ul>\n  <li>You can return your item within 42 days of receiving it, after chatting with our team, for a full refund or an exchange.</li>\n  <li>We do this because we believe in and stand by our product, and you’ll have to have a pretty good reason for wanting to return it, and we’d like to honour that.</li>\n  <li>Why 42 days? Why not? Email <a href=\"mailto:bunnies@itsallfluff.com\" class=\"underline\">bunnies@itsallfluff.com</a> to tell us how you feel.</li>\n  <li>Be gentle, Fluff has feelings too.</li>\n</ul>"},{"key":"Free shipping over $50","heading":"Free Shipping","subheading":"Free Shipping over $50 in Aus","content":"<ul>\n  <li>Fluff ships products every Wednesday & Friday.</li>\n  <li>Free shipping for orders over $50 AUD.</li>\n  <li>Otherwise it's $10 AUD. Delivered by Australia Post in about about a week.</li>\n  <li>Express Shipping: It’s not free, but it is quick. About 1-2 days quick. And about $15 exactly.</li>\n  <li>Standard International: It’s $25, we can’t afford free yet. And takes around 7 - 14 working days.</li>\n  <li>(All timelines are subject to world pandemics).</li>\n</ul>"}],"upsells":[{"category":"Refills","handles":["face-oil-1-refill","face-oil-2-refill","face-oil-3-refill"],"heading":"Shop Refills","type":"Product"},{"category":"All","handles":["face-oil-1","face-oil-2","bronzing-powder-refill","lip-oil-refill"],"heading":"Best Sellers","type":"Product"}],"sections":[{"type":"swipeImage","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1.471264367816092,"src":"/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/26852/pdp-triplet-how-to.jpg","srcSet":"/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/d64b1/pdp-triplet-how-to.jpg 256w,\n/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/89b9c/pdp-triplet-how-to.jpg 512w,\n/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/26852/pdp-triplet-how-to.jpg 1024w,\n/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/4d6da/pdp-triplet-how-to.jpg 1344w","srcWebp":"/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/e0f73/pdp-triplet-how-to.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/b42dd/pdp-triplet-how-to.webp 256w,\n/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/e4e36/pdp-triplet-how-to.webp 512w,\n/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/e0f73/pdp-triplet-how-to.webp 1024w,\n/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/9b8f4/pdp-triplet-how-to.webp 1344w","sizes":"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"}},"publicURL":"/static/6ee8b3caf6b1e519302be99dcc8aa906/pdp-triplet-how-to.jpg"},"heading":"How to use","text":"Step 1: Cleanse. Interchange Face Oil #1 and #2 as desired. As a lighter oil, Face Oil #1 is suitable for every day use for all skin types, whereas Face Oil #2 is a thicker oil, and is nice at night or for dehydrated skin."},{"type":"textImage","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":0.6368159203980099,"src":"/static/b40f7f905f61b52de6b1ff7045c33f6a/3817b/pdp-face-oil-3-atf-carousel-02.jpg","srcSet":"/static/b40f7f905f61b52de6b1ff7045c33f6a/d64b1/pdp